Please add the ability to Electronically "Sign" confluence pages.  

My organization is using confluence for requirements management, and we are struggling to find a way to capture sign-offs when the requirements are complete.

This could be accomplished with a new plugin that adds a new "Add Digitally Signature" option to the tools menu and a "Remove Digital Signature" option if you've already signed.  Also an accompanying macro to display digital signatures would be useful that either shows all digital signatures, or a signature for a particular user.  It would also be nice to set what users must sign a page.  

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of 29th February 2016|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
We do not have any plans to implement this in the foreseeable future. In order to set expectations correctly, we're closing this request now. 
There are a number of [Marketplace|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/search?application=confluence&q=approve] add-ons which provide this functionality.
Thank you for your votes and comments on this issue, along with your ongoing patience.

Regards,
Confluence Product Management
{panel}

